Virginia Verrill https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Virginia_Verrill 0 Virginia Verrill ( November 20, 1916 - January 18, 1999) was a singer in the era of old-time radio and big bands. Her work included providing the off-screen singing voices for some female film stars.
